The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Aug. 24: Oil India Ltd plans to hit the market with an initial public offer on September 7 with a price band of Rs 950-1,050 per share. The issue, which will close on September 11, plans to raise up to Rs 4,982 crore. The price band was fixed by a group of ministers headed by finance minister Pranab Mukherjee this evening.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 24: The Indian Railways has announced a reduction in tatkal charges, effective from October 1. The new tatkal charges will be levied at 10 per cent of the basic fare for second class and 30 per cent of basic fare for all other classes, said an official release. According to the revised charges, passengers will have to pay Rs 10-15 in second class. Reserved berth in a sleeper class will cost between Rs 75 and Rs 150. Tatkal charges for AC chair car will range between Rs 75 and Rs 150. In AC three tier it will range between Rs 200 and Rs 300.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 24: The government has barred large and bulk sugar consumers from keeping more than 15 days of stocks with them. The move will check hoarding and price escalation ahead of Dussehra and Diwali.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 24: Finance minister Pranab Mukherjee said India was not interested in fishing expedition of details of money stashed with Swiss banks but would work on specific cases.                                                                                                                           
